<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>3247</id>
	<title>Reader: handle gaps between posts</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">With high-traffic tags, or with users who don't sync very often, gaps may exist between the most recent existing post and the ones just retrieved from the server.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">These gaps mean the user is missing posts.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Detect when these gaps occur and provide a way for the user to load the missing posts, similar to how Twitter handles this situation.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">See [this PR](https://github.com/wordpress-mobile/WordPress-iOS/pull/4311) for @aerych's solution to this issue on iOS.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
